                            <comment id="484035" author="simmonsja" created="Thu, 15 Jan 2026 14:24:34 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;One more patch is needed to support the new fs 0context parameter handling.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="483922" author="gerrit" created="Thu, 15 Jan 2026 02:48:44 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&quot;Oleg Drokin &amp;lt;green@whamcloud.com&amp;gt;&quot; merged in patch &lt;a href=&quot;https://review.whamcloud.com/c/fs/lustre-release/+/60706/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://review.whamcloud.com/c/fs/lustre-release/+/60706/&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
Subject: &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-19230&quot; title=&quot;User linux kernel fs_context API&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-19230&quot;&gt;LU-19230&lt;/a&gt; obdclass: migrate from mount to fs_context API&lt;br/&gt;
Project: fs/lustre-release&lt;br/&gt;
Branch: master&lt;br/&gt;
Current Patch Set: &lt;br/&gt;
Commit: edfe64401c4310c0893802e5676b5fe6d680e01a&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="483157" author="simmonsja" created="Thu, 8 Jan 2026 18:36:01 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;There is a new fscontext API in user land (see man fsconfig). The new API breaks up the old mount handling into 2 separate steps. One to setup the file system and the second to do the actual mount. This is the default API used internally to libmount so if we can use that library to handle tuning the file system.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="482725" author="JIRAUSER18483" created="Tue, 6 Jan 2026 09:56:55 +0000"  >&lt;blockquote&gt;&lt;p&gt;This can replace the current approach Lustre uses to tune a file system with tunefs with a universal standard approach.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;James, could you elaborate what how this would look like?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="481974" author="simmonsja" created="Sat, 20 Dec 2025 16:29:17 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;We will need another patch to allow user land management for mount options.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
